		"name": "Bug Bounty Platform API",
		"description": "Complete API documentation for Bug Bounty Platform.\n\n**Base URL:** `http://localhost:5544`\n\n## Features\n\n- User Authentication (Company & Developer roles)\n    \n- Bug Management (Create, List, View)\n    \n- Solution Submission System\n    \n- Approve/Reject Workflow\n    \n- Balance Management\n    \n\n## Testing Flow\n\n1. Register Company → Add Balance\n    \n2. Create Bug with bounty\n    \n3. Register Developer → Submit Solution\n    \n4. Company: Approve/Reject\n    \n5. Check balances updated\n    \n\n## Authentication\n\nMost endpoints require Bearer token in Authorization header.  \nGet token from Register/Login responses.\n\n## Roles\n\n- **Company:** Can post bugs, add balance, approve/reject solutions\n    \n- **Developer**: Can submit solutions and earn bounties",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
		"_exporter_id": "35587072"
	},
